---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuickSummary from '../../components/QuickSummary.astro';
---

<Layout title="Speedup Calculator" description="Total up your Last War: Survival speedup inventory and see whether it covers a build, research, or training target.">
  <h1>Speedup Calculator</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-[#8a96b0]">Count your speedups, get total time by category, and see if it covers your next big upgrade. Counts save in your browser. Last verified: July 2026.</p>

  <QuickSummary>
    <p><strong>Spend rule:</strong> speedups are VS points waiting to happen — hoard them, then burn each category on the VS day whose theme matches it (construction Tuesday, research Wednesday, healing Saturday), inside the matching Arms Race phase slot for that day. Friday (Total Mobilization) scores everything, including training, so it's the best day to dump whatever's left over. See the day table below and the <a href="/events" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">VS &amp; Arms Race guide</a> for the full weekly sync.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>Your Inventory</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">Enter counts per denomination for each category. Universal speedups work on anything, so they're totaled separately and added where needed.</p>
  <div class="table-wrapper mt-2">
    <table>
      <caption class="sr-only">Speedup counts by category and denomination</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr><th scope="col">Category</th><th scope="col">1m</th><th scope="col">5m</th><th scope="col">15m</th><th scope="col">30m</th><th scope="col">1h</th><th scope="col">3h</th><th scope="col">8h</th><th scope="col">24h</th><th scope="col">Total</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody id="inv-body"></tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Does It Cover Your Target?</h2>
  <div class="my-4 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#2a3854] bg-[#0e1730]">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 items-end text-sm">
      <label>Category<br/>
        <select id="target-cat" class="chest-input" style="width:auto">
          <option value="construction">Construction</option>
          <option value="research">Research</option>
          <option value="training">Training</option>
          <option value="healing">Healing</option>
        </select>
      </label>
      <label>Days<br/><input type="number" min="0" value="0" id="t-days" class="chest-input" /></label>
      <label>Hours<br/><input type="number" min="0" value="0" id="t-hours" class="chest-input" /></label>
      <label>Minutes<br/><input type="number" min="0" value="0" id="t-mins" class="chest-input" /></label>
    </div>
    <div id="target-result" class="text-sm mt-3" role="status" aria-live="polite"></div>
  </div>

  <h2>When To Spend Each Category</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">Each VS day scores a different category. Spend the matching speedups that day — see the <a href="/events" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">VS &amp; Arms Race guide</a> for the full day table, point values, and hoard/prepare advice.</p>
  <div class="table-wrapper mt-2">
    <table>
      <caption class="sr-only">VS day, theme, and which speedup category to spend that day</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr><th scope="col">Day</th><th scope="col">VS theme</th><th scope="col">Spend here</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><th scope="row">Mon</th><td>Radar Training</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Tue</th><td>Base Expansion</td><td>Construction speedups</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Wed</th><td>Age of Science</td><td>Research speedups</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Thu</th><td>Train Heroes</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Fri</th><td>Total Mobilization</td><td><em>Everything</em> scores &mdash; best single day to dump saved speedups, training included</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Sat</th><td>Enemy Buster</td><td>Healing speedups</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p class="text-xs text-[#8a96b0] mt-1">Arms Race rotates five ~4-hour phases through each day &mdash; it isn't one all-day theme &mdash; so time your spend inside the phase slot that matches the day's VS theme (e.g. Tuesday's Base Expansion syncs with the Base Building phase), not just anywhere on the right day. Check your in-game calendar for the exact slot.</p>

  <h2>Notes</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Denominations:</strong> 1m/5m/1h/3h/8h are corroborated across independent sources. 15m/30m/24h are kept in the tool (removing them would break saved counts) but we couldn't independently confirm those three sizes exist as standalone speedup items &mdash; flagged as unconfirmed pending an in-game check. Event rewards occasionally add odd sizes too; count them under the nearest denomination or add the minutes to your target instead.</li>
    <li>The coverage check assumes universal speedups fill any gap after category-specific ones — that matches in-game behavior (the game consumes specific speedups first when you choose them, but universals apply anywhere).</li>
    <li>This tool does math only — no scraped upgrade-duration tables to go stale. Read your target's remaining time straight from the in-game timer. The 1-speedup-minute = 1-in-game-minute conversion is the standard assumption across this genre of game, not something we've independently verified for Last War specifically.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Where These Numbers Come From</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>The five categories (construction, research, training, healing, universal) are corroborated across multiple sources and match in-game speedup item types.</li>
    <li>The denomination list is partially confirmed: 1m/5m/1h/3h/8h appear in 2+ independent sources; 15m/30m/24h are single-sourced or unsourced in our research pass and are pending in-game verification (see notes above).</li>
    <li>The day/theme mapping in the table above is cross-checked against the same sources used for the <a href="/events" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">VS &amp; Arms Race guide</a> — see that page for point values and full sourcing rather than duplicating it here.</li>
    <li>The underlying minute math (summing denomination counts, comparing to a target duration) is pure arithmetic — nothing here is a scraped duration table that can go stale.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mt-4 text-xs text-[#8a96b0]">Denomination and category data cross-checked July 2026 against lastwartutorial.com and cpt-hedge.com speedup references; the day-theme mapping follows lastwartutorial.com/duel-vs and lastwartutorial.com/arms-race, kept consistent with this site's VS &amp; Arms Race guide. Items noted above as unconfirmed are flagged, not guessed.</p>

  <script>
    const DENOMS = [1, 5, 15, 30, 60, 180, 480, 1440]; // minutes
    const CATS = ['construction', 'research', 'training', 'healing', 'universal'];
    const LABELS = { construction: 'Construction', research: 'Research', training: 'Training', healing: 'Healing', universal: 'Universal (any)' };

    function clampInt(value, min, max, fallback) {
      const n = parseInt(value, 10);
      if (Number.isNaN(n)) return fallback;
      return Math.min(max, Math.max(min, n));
    }

    // Clamp AND normalize the visible input so the UI never shows a value
    // different from what the math uses (review feedback on PR #27).
    function readClamped(el, min, max, fallback) {
      const n = clampInt(el.value, min, max, fallback);
      if (el.value !== '' && String(n) !== el.value) el.value = String(n);
      return n;
    }

    function fmtMins(total) {
      const d = Math.floor(total / 1440);
      const h = Math.floor((total % 1440) / 60);
      const m = total % 60;
      const parts = [];
      if (d) parts.push(d + 'd');
      if (h) parts.push(h + 'h');
      if (m || parts.length === 0) parts.push(m + 'm');
      return parts.join(' ');
    }

    // Build the input grid.
    const tbody = document.getElementById('inv-body');
    for (const cat of CATS) {
      const tr = document.createElement('tr');
      let cells = '<th scope="row">' + LABELS[cat] + '</th>';
      DENOMS.forEach((d, i) => {
        cells += '<td><input type="number" min="0" value="0" id="s-' + cat + '-' + i + '" class="chest-input" style="width:3.5rem" /></td>';
      });
      cells += '<td id="total-' + cat + '" class="font-semibold"></td>';
      tr.innerHTML = cells;
      tbody.appendChild(tr);
    }

    function catTotal(cat) {
      let mins = 0;
      DENOMS.forEach((d, i) => {
        mins += readClamped(document.getElementById('s-' + cat + '-' + i), 0, 99999, 0) * d;
      });
      return mins;
    }

    function recalc() {
      const totals = {};
      for (const cat of CATS) {
        totals[cat] = catTotal(cat);
        document.getElementById('total-' + cat).textContent = fmtMins(totals[cat]);
      }

      const cat = document.getElementById('target-cat').value;
      const target =
        readClamped(document.getElementById('t-days'), 0, 9999, 0) * 1440 +
        readClamped(document.getElementById('t-hours'), 0, 9999, 0) * 60 +
        readClamped(document.getElementById('t-mins'), 0, 99999, 0);
      const el = document.getElementById('target-result');
      if (target === 0) {
        el.textContent = 'Enter your target time (from the in-game timer).';
      } else {
        const available = totals[cat] + totals.universal;
        const diff = available - target;
        el.innerHTML = diff >= 0
          ? 'Covered: <strong>' + fmtMins(available) + '</strong> available (' + fmtMins(totals[cat]) + ' ' + LABELS[cat].toLowerCase() + ' + ' + fmtMins(totals.universal) + ' universal) vs ' + fmtMins(target) + ' needed — <strong>' + fmtMins(diff) + ' left over</strong>.'
          : 'Short by <strong>' + fmtMins(-diff) + '</strong>: ' + fmtMins(available) + ' available vs ' + fmtMins(target) + ' needed.';
      }
      requestSave();
    }

    let saveTimer = null;
    function requestSave() {
      if (saveTimer) clearTimeout(saveTimer);
      saveTimer = setTimeout(saveState, 300);
    }

    function saveState() {
      const state = { counts: {}, cat: document.getElementById('target-cat').value,
        d: document.getElementById('t-days').value, h: document.getElementById('t-hours').value, m: document.getElementById('t-mins').value };
      for (const cat of CATS) DENOMS.forEach((d, i) => { state.counts[cat + '-' + i] = document.getElementById('s-' + cat + '-' + i).value; });
      try { localStorage.setItem('wf-speedup-calc', JSON.stringify(state)); } catch (e) { /* private mode */ }
    }

    function loadState() {
      try {
        const raw = localStorage.getItem('wf-speedup-calc');
        if (!raw) return;
        const s = JSON.parse(raw);
        for (const key in s.counts || {}) {
          const el = document.getElementById('s-' + key);
          if (el) el.value = s.counts[key];
        }
        if (s.cat) document.getElementById('target-cat').value = s.cat;
        if (s.d) document.getElementById('t-days').value = s.d;
        if (s.h) document.getElementById('t-hours').value = s.h;
        if (s.m) document.getElementById('t-mins').value = s.m;
      } catch (e) { /* ignore corrupt state */ }
    }

    loadState();
    // Scope listeners to this tool's controls only (event delegation on the
    // grid body + the four target controls) so unrelated page inputs never
    // trigger recalcs or localStorage writes.
    tbody.addEventListener('input', recalc);
    for (const id of ['target-cat', 't-days', 't-hours', 't-mins']) {
      document.getElementById(id).addEventListener('input', recalc);
    }
    recalc();
  </script>

  <style>
    .chest-input {
      width: 5rem;
      background: #0b1220;
      border: 1px solid #2a3854;
      border-radius: 0.375rem;
      padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
      color: #e5e9f2;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
